In Docker, port forwarding (or port mapping) allows you to expose a containers internal port to the host
machine. This is useful when you want to access services running inside a Docker container from the
outside world (e.g., accessing a web server running in a container from your browser).
sudo docker run -d -it --name myh+pd h+pd
sudo docker ps
sudo docker run -d -it --name myh+pd1 -p 81:80 h+pd
sudo docker ps -a
